-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_returns.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate returns to one approved return per item (latest approved)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        return_id,
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY CASE WHEN status = 'approved' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END ASC,
            return_date DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
)
SELECT
    return_id,
    item_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- models/intermediate/int_items_with_returns.sql
```sql
-- Join order items with deduplicated returns to flag returned items
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.order_id,
        oi.product_id,
        CASE WHEN r.return_id IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_returned
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} r
        ON r.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

-- models/intermediate/int_items_with_categories.sql
```sql
-- Enrich items with product and category information
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        iwc.item_id,
        iwc.is_returned,
        p.product_id,
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_returns') }} iwc
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
        ON p.product_id = iwc.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

-- models/marts/fct_product_return_rates.sql
```sql
-- Calculate return rates by category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        category_name,
        COUNT(*) AS total_items_sold,
        SUM(is_returned) AS total_items_returned
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_categories') }}
    GROUP BY category_name
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    total_items_sold,
    total_items_returned,
    ROUND(CAST(total_items_returned AS DECIMAL(10,2)) / total_items_sold, 4) AS return_rate
FROM source
ORDER BY return_rate DESC
